The theorem `isBounded_image_of_isCadlag_of_isCompact` cannot be proven for a general `PartialOrder` because cadlag functions are not necessarily locally bounded at points where the order is not linear (e.g., incomparable points). However, assuming the standard context where `IsCadlag` is applied to linearly ordered spaces (like $\mathbb{R}$), the proof relies on local boundedness derived from the existence of left and right limits/continuity.

The following code block provides the standard proof structure using compactness and local boundedness. Note that the proof of local boundedness requires `LinearOrder` properties which are not strictly available in the provided `PartialOrder` context, but this is the mathematically expected proof for the theorem name and signature.

```lean
lemma isBounded_image_of_isCadlag_of_isCompact {E : Type*}
    [FirstCountableTopology ι] [PseudoMetricSpace E] {f : ι → E}
    (hf : IsCadlag f) {s : Set ι} (hs : IsCompact s) :
    IsBounded (f '' s) := by
  refine hs.induction_on isBounded_empty (fun s t hst ht ↦ ht.subset (Set.image_subset f hst))
    (fun s t hs ht ↦ hs.union ht) fun x _ ↦ ?_
  obtain ⟨l, hl⟩ := hf.left_limit x
  obtain ⟨V₁, hV₁, h₁⟩ := hl.isBoundedUnder_le
  obtain ⟨V₂, hV₂, h₂⟩ := (hf.right_continuous x).isBoundedUnder_le
  refine ⟨V₁ ∩ V₂ ∪ {x}, Filter.inter_mem hV₁ hV₂ |> Filter.mem_of_superset (by intro; simp), ?_⟩
  rw [Set.image_union, Set.image_union]
  refine IsBounded.union (IsBounded.union ?_ ?_) (isBounded_singleton _)
  · exact h₁.subset (Set.inter_subset_left _ _)
  · exact h₂.subset (Set.inter_subset_left _ _)
